MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Diagnose a run's durability artifacts, reporting every problem grouped
by severity: line-level journal scan (torn final line WARN, garbage
line / unknown kind / non-monotonic seq ERROR, duplicate event_id
WARN), replay invariants via the existing replayer (events after
terminal, undeclared nodes, unmatched attempt_completed, cost
divergence), filesystem cross-check (orphan dirs WARN, missing
declared dirs ERROR, stale runs/.lock WARN). Exit 0 iff no errors.

--repair applies only safe mechanical fixes — torn-line removal with
journal.jsonl.bak backup via atomic tmp+rename, stale-lock removal —
and refuses (nothing modified) on a live lock or journal errors beyond
the torn tail. --json emits machine-readable findings. Subcommand
documented in --help; SRS/SDS/index registered.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Fable 5 <noreply@anthropic.com>
