+### 3.8 Run Doctor (`state/doctor.ts`) — FR-E83
+
+- **Surface:** `runDoctor({workflowDir, runId, repair?, json?})` →
+  `{report, output, exitCode}`; CLI wiring `runs doctor [--workflow
+  <dir>] --run <id> [--repair] [--json]` in `cli.ts` (workflow falls
+  back to the FR-E78 resolver). Pure of stdout/exit so unit tests
+  drive it on fabricated run dirs (`state/doctor_test.ts`).
+- **Checks (every problem reported, grouped by severity):**
+  1. Line-level journal scan — torn final line WARN (expected crash
+     artifact; byte offset retained for repair); non-final garbage
+     line, unknown `kind` (via
+     `run-journal.ts::isKnownJournalEventKind`, an exhaustive
+     `Record<RunJournalEventKind, true>` mirror), non-monotonic `seq`
+     ERROR; duplicate `event_id` WARN.
+  2. Replay invariants — delegates to the existing
+     `replayRunJournal` (no second replayer) and inspects its result:
+     events after a terminal run event, lifecycle events for
+     undeclared nodes, `attempt_completed` without matching
+     `attempt_started` (keyed `node_id`+`iteration`), and replayed
+     `total_cost_usd` diverging from the per-node cost expectation
+     (last successful attempt cost per node, falling back to the
+     replayed node cost) — all ERROR.
+  3. Filesystem cross-check — declared dirs from
+     `node_directory_declared` (relpath after `runs/<runId>/`),
+     infra dirs (`logs`, `worktree`, `.hitl-inbox`) skipped: orphan
+     dir WARN, declared-but-missing dir ERROR; stale `runs/.lock`
+     naming this run with a dead PID WARN (via `lock.ts::readLockInfo`
+     + `isRunLive`).
+- **Exit contract:** 0 iff no ERRORs (and no repair refusal), else 1;
+  CLI usage errors exit 2.
+- **`--repair` (mechanical only):** torn final line — back up the
+  journal as `journal.jsonl.bak`, write the truncated content to a
+  tmp file, `rename` over the original (atomic); stale lock —
+  remove. Refuses, modifying nothing, when the run is active (live
+  lock) or the journal has errors beyond the torn final line.
+- **`--json`:** emits the `DoctorReport` (findings with
+  severity/code/message/evidence path, repairs, counts, `ok`).
