+# engine: `runs doctor` — journal health checker with mechanical repair
+
+## Goal
+
+Give operators a `flowai-workflow runs doctor` subcommand that diagnoses a
+run's durability artifacts (journal integrity, replay invariants, filesystem
+cross-check, stale lock) reporting every problem found, and — with `--repair`
+— applies only safe mechanical fixes (torn final journal line, stale lock),
+refusing anything that would require semantic guessing.
+
+## Overview
+
+### Context
+
+A run's only durable record is its append-only `journal.jsonl` (FR-E69),
+replayed via `src/state/run-journal.ts::replayRunJournal` to reconstruct
+`RunState`. Crashes, manual tampering, and engine bugs can leave a journal or
+the surrounding run directory degraded: torn final line (expected crash
+artifact), mid-file garbage, unknown event kinds, events after a terminal run
+event, undeclared-node lifecycle events, cost divergence, orphan/missing node
+directories, and stale `runs/.lock` files. Today the only diagnostics are
+replay exceptions, which stop at the first problem.
+
+### Current State
+
+- `src/state/run-journal.ts` — writer + replayer. Replay tolerates a torn
+  final line (`ignored_partial_tail`) and duplicate `event_id`s
+  (`ignored_duplicate_event_ids`); throws on mid-file garbage, mixed run ids,
+  and missing `run_started`.
+- `src/state/lock.ts` — `defaultLockPath(workflowDir)` =
+  `<workflowDir>/runs/.lock`; `readLockInfo`, `isRunLive(workflowDir, runId)`
+  (true iff lock names the run AND its PID is alive).
+- `src/state/state.ts` — `getRunDir(runId, workflowDir)` =
+  `<workflowDir>/runs/<runId>`; `getNodeDir` adds optional `<phase>/` segment.
+- `src/cli.ts` — manual `for`-loop argument parsing per subcommand
+  (`parseArgs`, `parseAnswerArgs`); subcommand dispatch in
+  `if (import.meta.main)`; `printUsage()` is the `--help` text.
+- Journal `node_directory_declared.node_dir` =
+  `<workflowDir>/runs/<runId>/[<phase>/]<nodeId>` (engine.ts:795-806).
+- No `runs` subcommand exists yet.
+
+### Constraints
+
+- The existing replayer is the single source of replay truth: doctor calls
+  `replayRunJournal` and inspects its result; it MUST NOT re-implement state
+  reconstruction. Line-level lexing of `journal.jsonl` (per-line JSON.parse to
+  find every malformed line, unknown kind, seq/event_id anomaly) is journal
+  *parsing*, not replay — replay is the application of events to a state
+  model, which stays delegated.
+- Reuse `src/state/` helpers for run/node/lock paths and lock parsing — no
+  duplicated path construction or lock-file knowledge.
+- Follow the existing `src/cli.ts` argument-parsing style; no new deps.
+- `--repair` is mechanical only: torn final line (backup `.bak`, atomic
+  tmp+rename rewrite) and stale-lock removal. Refuse (clear error, nothing
+  modified) when the run is active (live lock) or the journal has errors
+  beyond the torn final line.
+- Exit 0 when no ERRORs, exit 1 otherwise; usage errors exit 2 (matches
+  `runEngine`'s parse-error convention).
+- One `--run` per invocation; flags only; no compaction.
+- `deno task check` stays green; FR-E83 registered in
+  `documents/requirements-engine/01-execution-model.md` (durability/recovery
+  area) + SRS index + `documents/index.md`.
+
+### Severity decisions (where the request leaves judgment)
+
+- torn final line → WARNING (expected crash artifact; replayer tolerates).
+- duplicate `event_id` → WARNING (replayer dedupes).
+- non-monotonic `seq` → ERROR (writer assigns monotonic seq; violation means
+  tampering or an engine bug).
+- mid-file garbage, unknown `kind`, replay failure, events after terminal,
+  undeclared-node lifecycle, unmatched `attempt_completed`, cost divergence,
+  declared-but-missing dir → ERROR.
+- orphan node dir → WARNING (extra data; replay is unaffected).
+- stale lock → WARNING (per request).
+- Cost divergence semantics: the replayer recomputes `total_cost_usd` from
+  node snapshots on every lifecycle event, so "replayed total vs sum of
+  state-node costs" is true by construction. The meaningful divergence is the
+  journal's per-node attempt-level costs vs the replayed total: for each node,
+  expected cost = `cost_usd` of its LAST `attempt_completed` (matches engine
+  behaviour where node cost = final attempt's cumulative cost), falling back
+  to the replayed node cost for nodes without attempt costs; divergence of
+  the summed expectation from replayed `total_cost_usd` (tolerance 1e-9) is
+  an ERROR.
+
