+## Solution
+
+### Selected Variant
+
+Variant 2 — dedicated `src/state/doctor.ts` module with a pure, testable core
+plus thin CLI wiring. Chosen over (1) inline-in-`cli.ts` (untestable, bloats
+the entry point, breaks the domain-grouped layout) and (3) a pluggable fsck
+framework + MCP tool (over-engineering; batch mode explicitly out of scope).
+Doctor logic is journal/lock domain knowledge, so it belongs in `src/state/`
+next to `run-journal.ts` and `lock.ts`. Selected autonomously (benchmark
+non-interactive rule); rationale above.
+
+### Files to create / modify
+
+- **NEW `src/state/doctor.ts`** — core + formatting:
+  - `DoctorFinding { severity: "error" | "warning"; code: string;
+    message: string; path: string }`.
+  - `DoctorRepair { code: string; message: string; path: string }`.
+  - `DoctorReport { run_id, workflow_dir, findings, repairs, errors,
+    warnings, ok }`.
+  - `scanJournal(journalPath)` — line-level lexer: per-line `JSON.parse`,
+    torn-tail detection (last line, no trailing newline → WARNING
+    `torn_final_line`; otherwise ERROR `garbage_line`), unknown `kind`
+    (ERROR `unknown_event_kind`), non-monotonic `seq` (ERROR
+    `non_monotonic_seq`), duplicate `event_id` (WARNING
+    `duplicate_event_id`). Returns findings + parsed events + torn-tail
+    byte offset (for repair).
+  - `checkReplayInvariants(runDir, findings)` — calls `replayRunJournal`;
+    on throw → ERROR `replay_failed`. On success: ERROR
+    `event_after_terminal` per event after `run_completed`/`run_failed`/
+    `run_aborted`; ERROR `undeclared_node` per node with lifecycle events
+    but no `node_declared`; ERROR `unmatched_attempt` per
+    `attempt_completed` without a prior unconsumed `attempt_started`
+    (keyed by `node_id` + `iteration`); ERROR `cost_divergence` per the
+    semantics in Constraints.
+  - `checkFilesystem(workflowDir, runId, events, findings)` — declared
+    relpaths from `node_directory_declared` (suffix after
+    `runs/<runId>/`); disk scan of `getRunDir(runId, workflowDir)`
+    children (skip `logs`, `worktree`, `.hitl-inbox`, files); orphan =
+    WARNING `orphan_node_dir`; declared-missing = ERROR
+    `missing_declared_dir`; stale lock via `readLockInfo` +
+    `isRunLive` = WARNING `stale_lock`.
+  - `repairRun(...)` — refusal checks first (live lock via `isRunLive`;
+    any journal ERROR other than torn tail), then: torn tail → copy
+    journal to `journal.jsonl.bak`, write truncated content to
+    `journal.jsonl.tmp`, `Deno.rename` over original; stale lock →
+    `Deno.remove(defaultLockPath(workflowDir))`.
+  - `runDoctor({ workflowDir, runId, repair, json })` →
+    `{ output: string, exitCode: 0 | 1 }` — pure of stdout/Deno.exit so
+    tests never spawn a subprocess.
+  - `formatReport(report)` — sections ERROR / WARNING / OK summary.
+- **`src/state/run-journal.ts`** — export `isKnownJournalEventKind(kind)`
+  backed by an exhaustive `Record<RunJournalEventKind, true>` so journal
+  kind knowledge stays in the journal module.
+- **`src/cli.ts`** — `parseRunsDoctorArgs(args)` (manual loop, same style as
+  `parseAnswerArgs`; flags `--workflow <dir>`, `--run <id>`, `--repair`,
+  `--json`; `--workflow` falls back to `resolveActiveWorkflow` per FR-E78;
+  missing `--run` → usage error); `runRunsDoctor(args)` handler (exit 2 on
+  usage error); dispatch branch for `runs` subcommand (`runs doctor …`,
+  unknown sub-subcommand → usage error); `printUsage()` gains the
+  `runs doctor` line + options.
+- **NEW `src/state/doctor_test.ts`** — fabricated run dirs in temp dirs using
+  `RunJournalWriter` (same pattern as `lifecycle-replay_test.ts`), covering
+  every case in the DoD list; live-lock refusal uses `Deno.pid` (own process
+  = alive), stale lock uses an impossible PID (e.g. 99999999).
+- **Docs** — FR-E83 section in
+  `documents/requirements-engine/01-execution-model.md`; index entries in
+  `documents/requirements-engine.md` and `documents/index.md`; SDS note in
+  `documents/design-engine/04-data-and-logic.md` (doctor surface next to the
+  journal replay contract).
+
+### Error handling strategy
+
+Doctor never throws for diagnosable states — every problem becomes a finding.
+It throws (→ CLI exit 2) only for usage errors and unexpected I/O failures
+(permissions etc., fail-fast). Repair refusals are explicit errors printed
+before anything is modified; repair operations are ordered backup → tmp →
+rename so a crash mid-repair never loses the original journal.
+
+### Verification commands
+
+- `deno task test src/state/doctor_test.ts`
+- `deno task test src/cli_test.ts src/state/`
+- `deno task check`
+
+## Follow-ups
+
+- (deferred) Expose doctor as an MCP tool for embedded hosts.
+- (deferred) Multi-run batch mode (`runs doctor --all`) — explicitly out of
+  scope in the request.
